The paper focuses on the analysis of hardware and software implementations of cryptographic algorithms, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the synergy between hardware and software, which could be related to computer architecture (cs.AR) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper proposes a statistical framework that can be customized for any area of application, which could be related to software engineering (cs.SE) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
